NAME
    App::calx - Display a calendar

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.005 of App::calx (from Perl
    distribution App-calx), released on 2019-03-26.

SYNOPSIS
     # See calx script provided in this distribution

DESCRIPTION
    This module provides the calx which, like the Unix utility cal, displays
    calendar on the command-line. The difference is, calx can also show and
    highlight dates from one or more Calendar::Dates modules.

FUNCTIONS
  gen_calendar
    Usage:

     gen_calendar(%args) -> [status, msg, payload, meta]

    Generate one or more monthly calendars in 3-column format.

    This function is not exported.

    Arguments ('*' denotes required arguments):

    *   highlight_today => *bool* (default: 1)

    *   month => *int*

        The first month.

        Not required if months=12 (generate whole year from month 1 to 12).

    *   months => *int* (default: 1)

    *   time_zone => *str*

    *   year* => *int*

    Returns an enveloped result (an array).

    First element (status) is an integer containing HTTP status code (200
    means OK, 4xx caller error, 5xx function error). Second element (msg) is
    a string containing error message, or 'OK' if status is 200. Third
    element (payload) is optional, the actual result. Fourth element (meta)
    is called result metadata and is optional, a hash that contains extra
    information.

    Return value: (any)

  gen_monthly_calendar
    Usage:

     gen_monthly_calendar(%args) -> any

    Generate a single month calendar.

    Return [\@lines, \@hol]

    This function is not exported.

    Arguments ('*' denotes required arguments):

    *   caldates_modules => *array[perl::modname]*

    *   highlight_today => *bool* (default: 1)

    *   month* => *int*

    *   show_next_month_days => *bool* (default: 1)

    *   show_prev_month_days => *bool* (default: 1)

    *   show_year_in_title => *bool* (default: 1)

    *   time_zone => *str*

    *   year* => *int*

    Return value: (any)

